# Copy to .env for local work. Production values live in the Vercel dashboard, never in a file.
# Never commit real values. If a secret is pasted somewhere it should not be, rotate it.
#
# THIS FILE DESCRIBES LOCAL DEVELOPMENT ONLY.
#
# Local points at Postgres on this machine. Production points at Supabase, and only Vercel knows
# those values. That separation is the point: it should be impossible to reach live customer data
# from a laptop, so `migrate reset` and `seed.mjs` are always safe to run here. See
# docs/ENVIRONMENTS.md.

# --- Database (local Postgres) --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Both URLs are the same locally: there is no pgBouncer in front of a local server, so the pooled
# and direct connections are one and the same. They differ only in production.
#
# DIRECT_URL still has to be set - the Prisma CLI reads it for migrate and studio.
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/operyx_dev?schema=public"
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/operyx_dev?schema=public"

# --- Auth ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Signs session cookies. Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
# The app refuses to start in production without it. Changing it signs everyone out.
AUTH_SECRET="replace-with-a-long-random-secret"

# NOTE: NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL, ROOT_DOMAIN and MESSAGING_PROVIDER used to be listed here. Nothing in
# the codebase reads them - they are left over from an earlier design. Setting them does nothing, so
# they are gone rather than kept as cargo. Add them back when something actually reads them.

# --- Storage ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# "local" writes to disk, which a serverless filesystem does not keep between invocations.
# Production needs "s3" (Supabase Storage speaks the S3 API).
STORAGE_PROVIDER="local"
# S3_ENDPOINT="https://PROJECT.supabase.co/storage/v1/s3"
# S3_REGION="ap-south-1"
# S3_BUCKET="operyx"
# S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=""
# S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=""
# S3_FORCE_PATH_STYLE="true"

# --- Invoice PDF --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local only. Production uses the bundled @sparticuz/chromium build; locally the PDF route drives
# the Chrome already installed on the machine. Set CHROME_PATH only if it cannot be found.
# CHROME_PATH="C:\Program Files\Google\Chrome\Application\chrome.exe"
